    "description": "Manya Group South Asia Partners, one of India's leading organizations, is hiring a Curriculum Developer for our Surat operations. We offer a competitive salary package along with world-class benefits.\n\nAbout Manya Group South Asia Partners:\nManya Group South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Design formative and summative assessments aligned to learning objectives\n• Conduct doubt-clearing sessions and remedial classes for weak students\n• Maintain classroom discipline and create a positive learning environment\n• Maintain student records and prepare progress reports\n• Conduct parent-teacher meetings and update parents on student performance\n• Participate in school events, workshops, and training programs\n• Coordinate with academic counselors for student career guidance\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Bloom's Taxonomy\n• Proficiency in LMS Platforms\n• Proficiency in Mentoring\n• Proficiency in Zoom/Teams\n• Proficiency in Content Creation\n• Proficiency in Child Psychology\n• Proficiency in Classroom Management\n• Proficiency in Pedagogy\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Surat, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Manya Group South Asia Partners!",
